The ANC in the Northern Cape is rolling out the red carpet for thousands of party members. KIMBERLEY - The ANC in the Northern Cape is rolling out the red carpet for thousands of party members. The liberation movement will celebrate its 108th birthday in the mining town of Kimberley. The National Executive Committee will be meeting for the first time this year. READ: ANC readies for its 108th birthday A series of events leading up to the main celebration have been planned as the party works to mobilise support. But, the mineral-rich province faces many challenges ranging from a high unemployment rate to poverty and crime. Over the weekend, thousands of party faithful will descend to the city to listen to the NEC’s January 8 Statement to be delivered by President Cyril Ramaphosa.